properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 31 at 9:40PM CST by NWS Aberdeen SD
properties.description:
Breezy winds out of the west gusting 20 to near 40 mph will
create patchy blowing and drifting snow. The main impact will
likely be across Interstate 29, south of Sisseton to near Summit.
Around the Peever area, winds will be strongest, with snow likely
covering the road at times, especially near overpasses.

Travel impacts are possible due to slick and sporadic snow
covered roads. Take extra precautions if you pan to travel, and
plan for quick changes in road conditions.

NWSheadline: Drifting Snow Over Portions Of INTERSTATE 29 This Evening
